  <h2><a href="../node/158/index.html" title="Announce: eViacam 1.6.0">Announce: eViacam 1.6.0</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Fri, 11/16/2012 - 19:14 — admin</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <h2>What is eViacam ?</h2>
<p>Enable Viacam (eViacam ) is a mouse replacement software that moves the pointer as you move your head. It works on standard PCs equipped with a web camera.</p>
<h2>What's new for eViacam v1.6.0 ?</h2>
<p>Enable Viacam has been awarded a second prize in VI Premio Vodafone a la Innovación en Telecomunicaciones 2012</p>
<ul>
<li>New features:
<ul>
<li>Integrated checking for updates feature</li>
<li>New drag&amp;drop sound feedback</li>
<li>Added -d command line flag</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Improved "About" dialog aesthetics</li>
<li>Fixed bug [ID:3548107]: allow higher smoothing values</li>
<li>Fixed: Russian help not available on linux</li>
<li>Translations updated: ca, es, de, fr, gl, he, pt_BR &amp; ru. Thanks to:
<ul>
<li>Christian Bieder (de)</li>
<li>Sébastien Lecointre (fr)</li>
<li>Miguel Bouzada (gl)</li>
<li>Yaron Shahrabani (he)</li>
<li>Wellyngton de Oliveira (pt_BR)</li>
<li>Sergey Shkurat (ru)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2>Where can I get it ?</h2>
<p>Sources and Win32 binaries can be downloaded from:<br /><a href="http://viacam.org/">http://viacam.org</a><br /><br />To install on <strong>Ubuntu</strong> open a terminal and run:<br />sudo add-apt-repository ppa:cesar-crea-si/eviacam<br />sudo apt-get update<br />sudo apt-get install eviacam<br /><br />Git repository:<br />git://eviacam.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/eviacam/eviacam</p>
<p></p>  </div>

